.Dd January 10, 1993
.Dt SIGPENDING 2
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm sigpending
.Nd return the set of pending signals
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Fd #include <signal.h>
.Ft int
.Fn sigpending "const sigset_t *set"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Fn sigpending
function returns the current set of blocked signals to the location
descibed by the single argument.
.Sh RETURN VALUES
A 0 value indicated that the call succeeded.  A -1 return value
indicates an error occurred and
.Va errno
is set to indicated the reason.
.Sh ERRORS
The
.Fn sigpending
currently only returns zero. In subsequent implementations that allow
more than 32 signals, this may change.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr kill 2 ,
.Xr sigaction 2 ,
.Xr sigsetops 3 ,
.Xr sigsuspend 2
.Sh STANDARDS
The
.Nm sigpending
function call is expected to
conform to
.St -p1003.1-88 .
